strictive gender and class hierarchies. Through pioneering analysis of the agendas of medical experts, police, socialists, feminists, legal reformers, and even serial killers, this volume puts forth a neglected history of the state of domestic service discourse at the turn of the 19th century and how it shaped and continues to shape the surveillance of women.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aHousehold employeesxLegal status, laws, etc.zAustriazViennaxHistory. 0aWomen household employeeszAustriazViennaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Austria & Hungary.2bisacsh  aHistory: 18th/19th Century, Refugee and Migration Studies, Gender Studies and Sexuality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831109977050 cprintz978180073993240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978180073994940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781800739949423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781800739949/original  a978-3-11-099770-5  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles